concept_explanation.fast_slow:
**Fast/Slow runner pattern:**

```java
// Find MIDDLE of linked list:
ListNode slow = head, fast = head;
while (fast != null && fast.next != null) {
    slow = slow.next;       // 1 step
    fast = fast.next.next;  // 2 steps
}
// When fast reaches end: slow is at middle
// Odd length [1,2,3,4,5]: slow=3 (true middle)
// Even length [1,2,3,4]: slow=3 (second middle)

// Detect CYCLE:
slow = head; fast = head;
while (fast != null && fast.next != null) {
    slow = slow.next; fast = fast.next.next;
    if (slow == fast) return true; // cycle detected!
}
return false;
// Why it works: in a cycle, fast gains 1 step per iteration
// → will eventually lap slow and meet
```

